<TITLE> Khaleda gets 6-month bail extension </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 19 (bdnews24.com) - A Dhaka court has given a six-month bail extension to former prime minister and current opposition leader Khaleda Zia in the Barapukuria coalmine graft case. AK Roy of Dhaka special judge's court-2 gave the extension Thursday in line with a High Court order. Khaleda's lawyers Zakir Hossain Bhuiyan and Joynal Abedin Mesbah produced the HC order, on which the judge extended the BNP chairperson's bail period to Sep 11. The Anticorruption Commission filed the graft case against the former premier with Shahbagh police on Feb 26 last year. Charges were pressed against Khaleda and 15 others on Oct 5. The ACC accused them of causing state losses totalling Tk 158.713 crore. b
